sentences: Frank Hamilton (born August 3, 1934) is an American folk musician, collector of folk songs, and educator.
He was a member of the folk group The Weavers in the early 1960s, and appeared at the first Newport Folk Festival in 1959.

After many years of teaching, playing and singing in California he married a third time, and with his wife relocated to Atlanta, where he performs on jazz guitar and co-founded the Frank Hamilton School in 2015.
He returned to Los Angeles in 1953, and with Jack Elliott and Guy Carawan formed The Dusty Road Boys, who toured the Midwest.
In 1956, at the Gate of Horn folksong nightclub in Oak Park, Illinois, Hamilton met Win Stracke, who took an interest in his teaching career.

sentences: In 1957 Hamilton, Stracke and Greening recruited teachers and an organizer, rented a space, and founded the Old Town School of Folk Music.

He began learning and collecting folk songs, with a special interest in the music of the American South; he spent much of the late 1940s and early 1950s traveling there, performing in bars and on street corners.
He was a member of the folk group The Weavers in the early 1960s, and appeared at the first Newport Folk Festival in 1959.
He was the house musician – playing guitar and other folk instruments – for Chicago's Gate of Horn, the nation's first folk music nightclub.

After many years of teaching, playing and singing in California he married a third time, and with his wife relocated to Atlanta, where he performs on jazz guitar and co-founded the Frank Hamilton School in 2015.
Early days ==
In 1956, at the Gate of Horn folksong nightclub in Oak Park, Illinois, Hamilton met Win Stracke, who took an interest in his teaching career.
section: == Chicago Old Town School of Folk Music ==

sentences: In Dawn Greening's dining room in Oak Park, Hamilton began teaching a group of 15 instrumentalists.
section: == Chicago Old Town School of Folk Music ==

sentences: Atlanta years ==
After decades of living in California, in 1985 Hamilton married Mary Susan Doyle Smith; she became a supportive stepmother to his son Evan from an earlier marriage.
Bob Bakert, a friend of Frank's, volunteered to serve as Master of Ceremonies for the memorial concert for her, at Steve's Live Music in Sandy Springs.
Together, they co-founded Frank Hamilton School in the fall of 2015 in Atlanta, but the school soon outgrew its first location; this had also occurred in Chicago.
Under the leadership of Hamilton and Shelley Satonin-Hershkovits, the school now meets in eight-week sessions at the Oakhurst Baptist Church in Decatur.
